  "texts": [
    "• Tracking context length: Depending on the language model, input prompts may have different lengths, from thousands, to tens of thousands to a million tokens.",
    "This means that, for large prompts submitted to a small language model, parts of the prompt may need to be summarized so that they can fit in the available context window.",
    "Rather than pruning prompt for a given maximum length a priori, we may adapt the prompt length to a given particular language model.",
    "• Ordering of information within the prompt: The Claude prompting guide recommends placing long context information before the instructions and examples, while Geminifoot_4 recommends trying different orders.",
    "• Including output prefixes: Some prompt engineering guides recommend including a prefix, a fragment of the expected output, at the end of the prompt."
  ],
